text.Taxonomy and naming:
Boronia barkeriana was first formally described in 1880 by Ferdinand von Mueller and the description was published in Fragmenta phytographiae Australiae from a speciment collected by "Mrs. C.A. Barker" near Mount Wilson.There are three subspecies:
Boronia barkeriana subsp. angustifolia Duretto has egg-shaped sepals more than 3 mm (0.1 in) wide and leaves 12–23 mm (0.5–0.9 in) long and 4–9 mm (0.2–0.4 in) wide;
Boronia barkeriana F.Muell.subsp. barkeriana has triangular sepals 1.5–3 mm (0.06–0.1 in) wide and leaves 16–30 mm (0.6–1 in) long and 4–11 mm (0.2–0.4 in) wide;
Boronia barkeriana subsp. gymnopetala Duretto has triangular sepals 1.5–3 mm (0.06–0.1 in) wide and leaves 15–33 mm (0.6–1 in) long and 1.5–6.5 mm (0.06–0.3 in) wide.
